tourBios.carHigh:
Has played the Adams Tour and NGA Tour.

2014: Finished T71 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December...Was medalist at the second stage Q-School event at McKinney, Texas, topping the field by six shots on the strength of a final-round 65 in cold North Texas weather...Played in two Web.com Tour events, the United Leasing Championship (T56) and Price Cutter Charity Championship (missed cut).

2013: Made his PGA TOUR debut, at the FedEx St. Jude Classic. Missed the cut.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Earned 2008 All-American honors at Oklahoma State. One college victory came at that year's Linger Longer Championship...Was a 2008-09 All-Big 12 selection...Won the 2008 Sahalee Players Championship...In high school, won back-to-back 4A state championship individual titles. His senior-year title included a 62, the lowest score recorded in the state tournament. Won the tournament by 12.
tourBios.personal: Parents are Matt and Leanne Whitekiller...Has one brother, Shane...Earliest childhood golf memory is getting picked up from kindergarten to go play golf with his dad...If not a professional golfer, would be an architect...Played football for three years and basketball for four in high school...Favorite courses played are Shady Oaks in Fort Worth and North Berwick in Scotland...Lucky charm is a gold dollar featuring Sacagawea...Favorites include Oklahoma City Thunder, "NCIS," "Family Guy," "Remember the Titans," Kevin Durant, and steak...Most famous person he has met is New Orleans Saints' head coach Sean Peyton...Best sporting event attended is the Masters...Would like to trade places for a day with a musician "So I could play any instrument I wanted to."...Dream foursome would include Ben Hogan, Tiger Woods and Frank Sinatra...Not many people know he likes to sing and listen to 1980s music...Bucket list includes skydiving...Favorite quote is "A mule can try, but he'll never win the Kentucky Derby."...Twitter handle is twhitekiller21.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T31st in 2010 at the Price Cutter Charity Championship Presented by Dr Pepper.
